This paper is about computer vision models and their efficient inference on video streams. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the technique of model distillation, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves the use of semantic segmentation, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions a new video dataset, which could fall under the category of multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses the efficiency of inference, which could be relevant to robotics (cs.RO).
